A group of inmates have barricaded themselves inside a cell block at St Albans prison. Correctional services reaction teams and police are on site and in the process of gaining entry to the cell block in which about 48 inmates have barricaded themselves. Eastern Cape Correctional Services Regional Commissioner Nkosinath Breakfast said the incident stemmed from inmates refusing to eat. &#8220;We are going to gain entry and do a head count and take them to the dining hall,&#8221; he said. Breakfast said the situation was not violent. However ambulance and fire department officials are on standby in the even the situation escalates. This incident comes less than a week after three inmates were killed in a fight between inmates and warders on Boxing Day. More than 30 others including inmates and warders were injured. &nbsp; &nbsp; Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share